      • leftShiftCyclic

        public SDVariable leftShiftCyclic(String name,
                                  SDVariable x,
                                  SDVariable y)
        Bitwise left cyclical shift operation. Supports broadcasting. Unlike leftShift(String, SDVariable, SDVariable) the bits will "wrap around": leftShiftCyclic(01110000, 2) -> 11000001
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the output variable. May be null.
        x - Input to be bit shifted (must be an integer type)
        y - Amount to shift elements of x array (must be an integer type)
        Returns:
        Bitwise cyclic shifted input x

        Bitwise right cyclical shift operation. Supports broadcasting. Unlike rightShift(String, SDVariable, SDVariable) the bits will "wrap around": rightShiftCyclic(00001110, 2) -> 10000011
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the output variable. May be null.
        x - Input to be bit shifted (must be an integer type)
        y - Amount to shift elements of x array (must be an integer type)
        Returns:
        Bitwise cyclic shifted input x

      • bitsHammingDistance

        public SDVariable bitsHammingDistance(String name,
                                      SDVariable x,
                                      SDVariable y)
        Bitwise Hamming distance reduction over all elements of both input arrays.
        For example, if x=01100000 and y=1010000 then the bitwise Hamming distance is 2 (due to differences at positions 0 and 1)
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the output variable. May be null.
        x - First input array. Must be integer type.
        y - First input array. Must be integer type, same type as x
        Returns:
